About
I'm Pablo Ezcurra, a dual bachelor's student in Business Administration and Data & Business Analytics at IE University (Madrid), with a semester at the University of Maryland — Smith School of Business.
My interests sit at the intersection of financial markets and applied data science. This project came out of that combination: using Python to build a real data pipeline, test a hypothesis about prediction markets, and apply econometric methods to something I find genuinely interesting — how information flows into prices.
Outside this project I work as a Tech Sales Intern at Salesforce, where I build AI-powered sales agents and automate workflows using Agentforce and generative AI tools. I also hold a Bloomberg Market Concepts certification and have hands-on experience with Python, SQL, Power BI, and R.
